{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban zoos and fund more natural reserves and national parks",
        "additional_details": "Many animals in zoos show signs of stress, boredom, and abnormal repetitive behaviours.\r\n \r\nLarge-ranging species (e.g. elephants, big cats) cannot express natural behaviours in limited enclosures.\r\n \r\nMany wild animals evolved for vast territories, complex ecosystems, and natural social structures.\r\n \r\nEven accredited zoos cannot replicate the complexity of wild ecosystems.\r\n \r\nWe believe this conflicts with the spirit of the UK\u2019s high animal welfare standards under the Animal Welfare Act 2006.",
        "background": "The UK should prioritise protecting animals in their natural habitats rather than confining them for display. Parliament should phase out zoos and expand protected natural reserves and national parks.",
